      "lesson title": "AI in Drug Interaction Checks",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Artificial intelligence tools are increasingly being used in healthcare settings to help identify potentially harmful drug interactions, but they are not infallible. This lesson explores how AI can sometimes miss dangerous combinations or provide incomplete guidance, putting patients at risk if clinicians rely on it without question. You will look at real-world examples of where AI-driven interaction checks have fallen short, and why understanding these limitations is essential for anyone working in or around patient care. By the end of this lesson, you will feel more confident in recognising when AI advice should be verified against clinical expertise or additional resources. No prior technical knowledge is required, just an openness to thinking critically about the tools we use in modern healthcare.",
