          "slidetitle": "Gaps in AI Drug Alerts",
          "subtitle": "Where critical warnings fall short",
          "slidecontent": "• AI systems often miss interactions involving newer or rarely prescribed drugs not yet in their training data\n• Incomplete patient records mean the AI only checks what it can see\n• Some tools flag low-risk combinations but stay silent on genuinely dangerous ones\n• Polypharmacy cases (five or more drugs) can overwhelm alert logic\n• Alerts sometimes lack dosage context, making guidance too vague to act on\n• No built-in awareness of a patient's kidney or liver function, which changes everything"
